<item>
            <title>[LU-8629] Error exit path doing wrong cleanup in cl_env_percpu_init</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8629</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Upstream kernel guys found a bug in cl_env_percpu_init:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rc != 0) {
                /* Indices 0 to i (excluding i) were correctly initialized,
                 * thus we must uninitialize up to i, the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;rest&lt;/span&gt; are undefined. */
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (j = 0; j &amp;lt; i; j++) {
                        cle = &amp;amp;cl_env_percpu[i];
                        lu_context_exit(&amp;amp;cle-&amp;gt;ce_ses);
                        lu_context_fini(&amp;amp;cle-&amp;gt;ce_ses);
                        lu_env_fini(&amp;amp;cle-&amp;gt;ce_lu);
                }
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here clearly cle = &amp;amp;cl_env_percpu&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;i&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; should be cle = &amp;amp;cl_env_percpu&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;j&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
